searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"Msutils.Data.Types","doc":"Data types  for the mscmp_syst_utils_data component.","ref":"Msutils.Data.Types.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Msutils.Data.Types.common_validators/0","doc":"Establishes the known common changeset validator options.","ref":"Msutils.Data.Types.html#t:common_validators/0"},{"type":"module","title":"Msutils.Data","doc":"This is a set of utilities for working with data which is generally\nuseful across components.\n\n\n> #### Note {: .info}\n>\n> `Changeset Validators` do not check their `opts` parameter for validity.  This\n> is expected to be handled by the caller prior to calling these functions.  See\n> the `Msutils.Data.common_validator_options/1` macro for more information on\n> adding the standard options which can be used to validate changesets.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html"},{"type":"macro","title":"Msutils.Data.common_validator_options/1","doc":"Returns a NimbleOptions struct with the requested common validator options for\nuse with the Changeset validation functions from the Msutils.Data module.\n\nThe common validator options establish cross-Component standards for data\nlimits such as minimum and maximum lengths commonly used data fields.  In many\nways, these options act as constants for common Changeset validations.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#common_validator_options/1"},{"type":"macro","title":"Parameters - Msutils.Data.common_validator_options/1","doc":"* `selected_options` - selects the desired options from the common validator\n    option definitions.  This is in the form of a list of the desired options.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#common_validator_options/1-parameters"},{"type":"macro","title":"Select Options - Msutils.Data.common_validator_options/1","doc":"The following are accepted for selected options:\n\n  * `:internal_name`\n\n  * `:display_name`\n\n  * `:external_name`\n\n  * `:user_description`","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#common_validator_options/1-select-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Msutils.Data.validate_display_name/2","doc":"Changeset validation ensuring that the `display_name` field is valid and\nmeets minimum and maximum length requirements.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_display_name/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Msutils.Data.validate_display_name/2","doc":"* `changeset` - an `Ecto.Changeset` struct to be validated.\n\n  * `opts` - options which configure the validation checks of the functions.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_display_name/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Msutils.Data.validate_display_name/2","doc":"* `:min_display_name_length` (`t:pos_integer/0`) - Sets the minimum grapheme length of display_name values. The default value is `6`.\n\n* `:max_display_name_length` (`t:pos_integer/0`) - Sets the maximum grapheme length of display_name values. The default value is `64`.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_display_name/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Msutils.Data.validate_external_name/2","doc":"Changeset validation ensuring that the `external_name` field is valid and\nmeets minimum and maximum length requirements.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_external_name/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Msutils.Data.validate_external_name/2","doc":"* `changeset` - an `Ecto.Changeset` struct to be validated.\n\n  * `opts` - options which configure the validation checks of the functions.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_external_name/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Msutils.Data.validate_external_name/2","doc":"* `:min_external_name_length` (`t:pos_integer/0`) - Sets the minimum grapheme length of external_name values. The default value is `6`.\n\n* `:max_external_name_length` (`t:pos_integer/0`) - Sets the maximum grapheme length of external_name values. The default value is `64`.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_external_name/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Msutils.Data.validate_internal_name/2","doc":"Changeset validation ensuring that the `internal_name` field is valid and\nmeets minimum and maximum length requirements.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_internal_name/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Msutils.Data.validate_internal_name/2","doc":"* `changeset` - an `Ecto.Changeset` struct to be validated.\n\n  * `opts` - options which configure the validation checks of the functions.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_internal_name/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Msutils.Data.validate_internal_name/2","doc":"* `:min_internal_name_length` (`t:pos_integer/0`) - Sets the minimum grapheme length of internal_name values. The default value is `6`.\n\n* `:max_internal_name_length` (`t:pos_integer/0`) - Sets the maximum grapheme length of internal_name values. The default value is `64`.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_internal_name/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Msutils.Data.validate_syst_defined_changes/2","doc":"Changeset validation ensuring that, if the record is set as `syst_defined`,\nthe prohibited fields are not changed.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_syst_defined_changes/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Msutils.Data.validate_syst_defined_changes/2","doc":"* `changeset` - an `Ecto.Changeset` struct to be validated.\n\n  * `prohibited_fields` - a list of field names for which changes are\n    prohibited if the record is set as `syst_defined`.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_syst_defined_changes/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Msutils.Data.validate_user_description/2","doc":"Changeset validation ensuring that the `user_description` field is set if\nrequired and allowed and meets minimum and maximum length requirements.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_user_description/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Msutils.Data.validate_user_description/2","doc":"* `changeset` - an `Ecto.Changeset` struct to be validated.\n\n  * `opts` - options which configure the validation checks of the functions.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_user_description/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Msutils.Data.validate_user_description/2","doc":"* `:min_user_description_length` (`t:pos_integer/0`) - Sets the minimum grapheme length of user_description values. The default value is `6`.\n\n* `:max_user_description_length` (`t:pos_integer/0`) - Sets the maximum grapheme length of user_description values. The default value is `1000`.","ref":"Msutils.Data.html#validate_user_description/2-options"},{"type":"exception","title":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError","doc":"This module defines the macro related error types for the Msutils.Data module.","ref":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.new/3","doc":"Creates a new error struct with the given kind, message, and options.","ref":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.html#new/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.new/3","doc":"* `kind` - The kind of error, see `t:kinds/0` for the available Kinds.\n\n  * `message` - A string describing the error.\n\n  * `opts` - A keyword list of additional options.","ref":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.html#new/3-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.new/3","doc":"* `:context` - contextual information for better understanding the\n    error.  If provided, the context should be of type\n    `t:MscmpSystError.Types.Context.t/0`.\n\n  * `:cause` - The cause of the error, which can be an exception, an error tuple,\n    or any other term.","ref":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.html#new/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.new/3","doc":"Returns a struct of this error type with the error details.","ref":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.html#new/3-returns"},{"type":"type","title":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.kinds/0","doc":"Represents the available Kinds of error allowed by this Error type.","ref":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.html#t:kinds/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Available Kinds - Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.kinds/0","doc":"* `:invalid_option` - Defines errors where the selected options are invalid even though they\nare in the correct form.\n\n  * `:invalid_selector` - Defines errors where the parameter value is of an invalid type.","ref":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.html#t:kinds/0-available-kinds"},{"type":"type","title":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Mserror.Msutils.Data.MacroError.html#t:t/0"}],"content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":[48,46,51,52,46,50]}}